@jemenger Why not scale across more venues in the same city first? 

There was some venue fragmentation at EthDenver but the majority of folks were at the castle which was always super packed.

Should split up stages more and explicitly *let hackers/booths have their own location*

@pedrouid @RHLSTHRM @cosmos E.g. using tendermint POS as consensus layer for fees when decentralizing rollup sequencers.

Connext is planning to do something similar for fair routing/fees.

Both are infra usecases that require cheap DA and *cannot* (and probably should not) live in a smart contract.

@iamDCinvestor 100% agreed - the multisig bridges are a huge problem otherwise too and people should NOT be using them.

It's only a matter of time before we start seeing economic exploits in addition to smart contract ones like today.

Options like @nomadxyz_ are better.

@0xmirichael @alltejuupptaget @iamDCinvestor Eh? No, this is not really true.

Yes, many bridges are trusted (bc they rely on multisigs) and rollup bridges don't have this issue.

However, the implementation complexity of rollups and rollup bridges is FAR higher than a multisig.
